      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Isolate Claude OAuth usage from CLI refresh",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- prevent Claude OAuth usage fetches in CLI runtime from delegating token refresh through the local Claude CLI\n- preserve app/user-initiated Claude OAuth delegated repair for expired Claude-CLI-owned credentials\n- skip CLI version detection for Claude OAuth usage results so Waybar polling does not spawn CLI/MCP side effects\n- cover the OAuth delegated-refresh runtime gate on Linux-safe descriptor tests plus existing lower-level coverage\n\n## Root Cause\n\nWaybar invokes the CodexBar CLI repeatedly for Claude OAuth usage. That CLI path could still fall through to Claude CLI-backed delegated refresh and CLI version detection, which can spawn local MCP server launchers. On the affected Linux setup those Bun-backed MCP launches were aborting repeatedly, creating a Waybar/coredump loop.\n\n## Compatibility\n\nThe no-delegation behavior is scoped to CLI runtime. App/user-initiated Claude OAuth fetches can still use delegated refresh to repair expired Claude-CLI-owned credentials.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter ClaudeOAuthDelegatedRefreshLinuxTests`\n- `swift test --filter PlatformGatingTests`\n- `swift test`\n- `swift build`\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh lint-linux`\n- `swift build -c release`\n- Waybar script smoke check using the rebuilt CLI: exited 0, no stderr, Bun/MCP launcher process count stayed flat\n",
        "branch": "codex/claude-oauth-cli-isolation",
        "head_sha": "3c72adc51e6136a615c99e7e00971c1ddc980ecd",
